03:27.319 --> 03:29.470
<i>When I first got to McKinley, I
was afraid to make eye contact.</i>

03:29.521 --> 03:31.305
<i>I didn't talk
about my politics,</i>

03:31.356 --> 03:33.074
<i>I didn't share
what was in my heart</i>

03:33.141 --> 03:35.476
<i>I... oh, let's just call
the Cadillac pink</i>

03:35.527 --> 03:36.911
<i>and be done with it.</i>

03:36.978 --> 03:38.529
<i>I was in the closet.</i>

03:38.614 --> 03:41.499
<i>And most days,
I was also in the Dumpster.</i>

03:41.583 --> 03:43.334
<i>But McKinley has made me
a stronger,</i>

03:43.419 --> 03:46.421
<i>more socially conscious,
fashion-forward person.</i>

03:46.488 --> 03:48.589
<i>And perhaps
I played some small part</i>

03:48.657 --> 03:51.125
<i>in making it possible for
tadpole gays all over Lima</i>

03:51.176 --> 03:52.827
<i>to be themselves in public.</i>

03:52.878 --> 03:55.663
<i>Not a bad legacy for someone
who once pretended</i>

03:55.714 --> 03:57.265
<i>to be in lust with Rachel Berry</i>

03:57.332 --> 03:59.500
<i>so I wouldn't have to date
Mercedes Jones.</i>

03:59.551 --> 04:01.552
<i>Now if can just get through
the next few days</i>

04:01.637 --> 04:03.604
<i>without turning into a hot mess
teary train wreck.</i>

04:03.672 --> 04:04.522
(school bell rings)

04:04.606 --> 04:06.774
(door opens)
Ted...

04:06.842 --> 04:09.694
why on earth did you want
to meet me in here?

04:09.778 --> 04:11.479
Oh, my God-- my NYDADA letter
came, didn't it?

04:11.530 --> 04:12.530
Not yet.

04:12.614 --> 04:13.614
Sit down.
I want to give you

04:13.682 --> 04:14.565
your graduation present.

04:14.650 --> 04:15.683
Is Elaine Stritch here?

04:15.751 --> 04:17.067
I don't know who that is.

04:17.136 --> 04:19.620
See, this is the problem
with getting you gifts--

04:19.688 --> 04:21.856
I can't make heads or tails
about what it is your like.

04:21.906 --> 04:23.541
Dad, I'm easy.

04:23.609 --> 04:25.877
<i>Just get me something from Tom
Ford's Vanities in Vanity Fair.</i>

04:25.961 --> 04:27.562
Good to know.

04:27.629 --> 04:30.665
So... somewhere around
your seventh birthday,

04:30.716 --> 04:32.800
I lost you.

04:32.868 --> 04:34.669
Before that,
you were a normal kid.

04:34.720 --> 04:36.471
I mean, a kid who
liked to dust, but...

04:36.538 --> 04:38.806
You know, I read you to bed,

04:38.874 --> 04:42.209
I put cartoons on TV
when you were bored.

04:42.261 --> 04:43.811
I taught you how
to ride a bike...

04:43.879 --> 04:44.879
the normal stuff.

04:44.930 --> 04:48.232
And then you turned
seven or eight,

04:48.317 --> 04:51.185
and you start to become this.

04:51.236 --> 04:54.572
And, uh, it was like I was
living with an alien.

04:54.656 --> 04:57.825
I mean, I tried to keep up,
but, uh, you know,

04:57.893 --> 04:59.410
once your mom passed, I...
I really...

04:59.495 --> 05:00.745
I didn't stand a chance.

05:00.829 --> 05:02.246
You did good, Dad.

05:02.331 --> 05:05.666
I am proud of what you and I
did together.

05:05.734 --> 05:06.667
I'm proud of us, too.

05:06.735 --> 05:07.785
Do you remember when it started?

05:07.870 --> 05:10.121
When we turned a corner

05:10.205 --> 05:12.373
and started walking
towards each other,

05:12.424 --> 05:14.008
rather than in opposite
directions?

05:14.075 --> 05:15.259
Tell me.

05:15.344 --> 05:16.544
Aw, screw that,
I'm gonna show you.

05:16.595 --> 05:20.848
It was in the basement
of our old house.

05:20.916 --> 05:22.633
You were wearing
a unitard.

05:22.718 --> 05:25.186
Oh, God, Dad, please
don't do this--

05:25.253 --> 05:28.606
Sit down and accept
your present.

05:28.690 --> 05:29.941
