on an indie label.

10:56.296 --> 10:59.097
I'm going to be taking
extension classes at UCLA.

10:59.165 --> 11:02.134
If this was happening
to anyone else, I would be

11:02.185 --> 11:03.302
extremely jealous.

11:03.353 --> 11:05.637
This is really cool.

11:05.688 --> 11:07.606
Congratulations.
Thank you.

11:07.673 --> 11:08.974
(grunts)

11:09.025 --> 11:10.675
And I couldn't have done it
without you.

11:10.727 --> 11:13.695
Oh, did you hear
about Mike?

11:13.780 --> 11:16.231
I was all set to go
to Alvin Ailey,

11:16.316 --> 11:19.201
and then Joffrey in Chicago
offered me a scholarship.

11:19.285 --> 11:21.453
Oh, Mike, that's amazing.

11:21.520 --> 11:23.355
Congratulations.

11:23.406 --> 11:25.523
You must be so excited
to ditch that Cheerios! uniform

11:25.575 --> 11:27.292
and put on the one
for University of Louisville.

11:27.360 --> 11:29.578
Yeah, I... I can't wait.

11:29.662 --> 11:31.747
<i>SANTANA:
This is embarrassing.</i>

11:31.831 --> 11:35.801
<i>I'm a star, so what am I doing
heading to Kentucky?</i>

11:35.868 --> 11:38.003
<i>I'm just as talented
as Mercedes,</i>

11:38.054 --> 11:39.972
<i>Boy Chang, Berry
or Lady Hummel.</i>

11:40.039 --> 11:41.723
<i>Thank God for Mom.</i>

11:41.808 --> 11:44.176
<i>She'll know what to do.</i>

11:44.227 --> 11:47.596
<i>When Santana finally said,
"Mami, papi, I'm gay,"</i>

11:47.680 --> 11:49.564
all I could
think of was,

11:49.649 --> 11:51.099
I should have known.

11:51.184 --> 11:53.151
When she was eight,
she went trick-or-treating

11:53.219 --> 11:55.053
<i>as Uncle Jesse on Full House.</i>

11:55.104 --> 11:57.689
Spent two years
growing out that hair.

11:57.740 --> 11:59.224
"Business in the front..."

11:59.275 --> 12:01.226
BOTH:
"Party in the back."
Ew.

12:01.277 --> 12:03.028
So, you just really didn't care?

12:03.079 --> 12:04.579
I care that my baby's happy.

12:04.664 --> 12:06.865
<i>I wish abuela
felt the same.
I know.</i>

12:06.916 --> 12:08.066
<i>It sucks, mija.</i>

12:08.117 --> 12:09.334
But you don't want a
person in your life

12:09.402 --> 12:10.419
that doesn't support
your dreams.

12:12.005 --> 12:13.789
I don't want to go
to that cheerleading program

12:13.873 --> 12:15.123
at the University of Louisville.

12:15.208 --> 12:16.508
I want to go to New York.

12:16.575 --> 12:18.126
Go to college, Santana.

12:18.211 --> 12:20.128
Do what I never
got the chance to do.

12:20.213 --> 12:22.130
New York will
still be there

12:22.215 --> 12:24.049
after you've earned
your college degree.

12:24.100 --> 12:27.302
Brittany, I understand you
got into Purdue University?

12:27.387 --> 12:29.054
Not the university;
the poultry farm.

12:29.105 --> 12:30.973
Plucker is a steady profession.

12:31.057 --> 12:33.025
But I can't go to either
'cause I'm not graduating.

12:33.092 --> 12:34.142
What?
Yeah.

12:34.227 --> 12:35.477
I was kind of glad

12:35.561 --> 12:37.112
when I found out
that I was flunking

12:37.196 --> 12:38.263
because it'll give me a chance

12:38.314 --> 12:39.597
to do my senior year
all over again.

12:39.649 --> 12:41.650
And way better. I'll show up
to my classes this time.

12:41.734 --> 12:43.785
Plus, I'll get to be a two-term
senior class president.

12:43.870 --> 12:45.437
Why are you pretending
that this is okay?

12:45.488 --> 12:47.155
And why didn't you tell me?

12:47.240 --> 12:49.157
What did you think
was going to happen to me?

12:49.242 --> 12:51.710
I have a 0.0
grade point average.

12:51.777 --> 12:53.945
Well, maybe if Brittany's
staying in Lima,

12:53.997 --> 12:55.613
then I should stay, too.

