<i>♪ You've got the music in you. ♪</i>

15:32.738 --> 15:34.739
(school bell ringing)

15:36.576 --> 15:38.410
I don't know. I mean, when
you're looking at both of them,

15:38.461 --> 15:40.278
it's really hard to not just
want to go with the Chiavari.

15:40.329 --> 15:42.831
There's $20 difference
between each of those chairs.

15:42.915 --> 15:45.133
That's, like, hundreds
of dollars or something.

15:45.218 --> 15:46.668
We can't afford that.

15:46.752 --> 15:49.387
Look, I compromised on the food,
I compromised on the location,

15:49.455 --> 15:50.722
I compromised
on the flowers.

15:50.789 --> 15:52.307
Does my butt
really have to compromise

15:52.391 --> 15:53.625
on what it sits on?

15:53.676 --> 15:54.959
Maybe what you're
really upset about

15:55.011 --> 15:56.228
is that you're compromising
on your husband.

15:56.295 --> 15:57.512
Please, that
is the one thing

15:57.597 --> 15:58.847
that I don't have
any doubts about.

15:58.931 --> 16:00.515
Really?

16:00.600 --> 16:02.517
'Cause you've been kind of
giving me a weird vibe lately.

16:02.602 --> 16:04.519
No.

16:06.522 --> 16:07.822
You're just projecting,
all right?

16:07.907 --> 16:09.307
You're nervous about
finding out about school,

16:09.358 --> 16:10.642
and you're
putting it on me.

16:10.693 --> 16:12.477
Besides, when
did you become

16:12.528 --> 16:14.246
the one that I
was settling for?

16:14.313 --> 16:18.033
Look, I don't care who
gets in where, all right?

16:18.117 --> 16:21.169
I'm marrying you, and
nothing makes me happier.

16:21.254 --> 16:25.006
Even if we have to sit in
these ugly fold-out chairs.

16:26.459 --> 16:27.825
Okay?

16:27.877 --> 16:29.327
Okay.

16:31.181 --> 16:31.181
+

16:32.191 --> 16:34.225
<i>: I remember the first day
of school this year.</i>

16:34.276 --> 16:38.229
<i>I had no idea what I wanted
to do, who I was.</i>

16:38.280 --> 16:40.064
<i>It wasn't the past
I was scared of.</i>

16:40.115 --> 16:42.150
<i>I'd call my high school career
a total success.</i>

16:42.234 --> 16:44.101
<i>I mean, not in terms
of grades and stuff,</i>

16:44.153 --> 16:45.770
<i>but I won a state title
in football,</i>

16:45.821 --> 16:48.156
<i>a national championship
in Glee Club.</i>

16:48.240 --> 16:50.542
<i>I never hurt anyone real bad,
and it turns out I never</i>

16:50.609 --> 16:52.126
<i>actually accidentally
got anyone pregnant.</i>

16:52.211 --> 16:54.495
<i>It was the future
I was terrified of.</i>

16:54.580 --> 16:56.331
<i>But not anymore.</i>

16:56.415 --> 16:57.749
<i>I'm getting married
to a great girl.</i>

16:57.800 --> 16:59.634
<i>I'm moving to New York
to chase my dreams</i>

16:59.718 --> 17:00.885
<i>with her
and my gay stepbrother.</i>

17:00.953 --> 17:03.955
<i>And how do I know?</i>

17:04.006 --> 17:05.455
<i>InsauditionActors Studio</i>

17:05.507 --> 17:07.559
<i>with the main dude himself.</i>

17:07.626 --> 17:10.428
You're Finn Hudson, and
you want to be an actor.

17:10.479 --> 17:12.012
I was very moved

17:12.097 --> 17:13.598
by your letter
and application, Finn.

17:13.648 --> 17:15.516
You're no doubt aware
that you would be

17:15.601 --> 17:18.269
an exceptional case,
should we accept you.

17:18.319 --> 17:20.154
Yes.

17:20.239 --> 17:21.489
Why don't we start
with your, uh,

17:21.574 --> 17:22.807
dramatic monologue?

17:22.858 --> 17:24.909
Okay.

17:24.977 --> 17:27.829
<i>Yep, fear is no longer
in my vocabulary.</i>

17:27.913 --> 17:30.481
(school bell ringing)

17:30.532 --> 17:32.700
Hey. Just finishing up.

17:32.785 --> 17:34.669
Lay it on me.

17:34.753 --> 17:36.170
"Dear Finn, great knowing you.

17:36.255 --> 17:37.822
Will Schuester."
Are you kidding me?

17:37.873 --> 17:40.041
I'm, like, the best
man at your wedding.
It's not that bad.

17:40.125 --> 17:42.326
And you can't dictate
what I write in your yearbook.

17:42.378 --> 17:44.095
Yes, I can. I want a
little emotion in there.

17:44.162 --> 17:45.380
Some "son I never had"

17:45.464 --> 17:46.547
or "little brother" garbage
or something.

17:46.632 --> 17:48.099
Look, I-I wanted to. I...

17:48.166 --> 17:50.051
I started ten times,
and I couldn't get

17:50.135 --> 17:52.053
two words out
without falling apart.

17:52.137 --> 17:54.555
Well, I don't need a bunch
of "blah, blah" in a book

17:54.640 --> 17:55.840
to remember you anyway.

18:03.065 --> 18:04.899
Finn, wait.

18:04.967 --> 18:06.634
I-I need to tell you something.

18:06.702 --> 18:08.569
Something I would rather
not have

18:08.654 --> 18:09.954
written down anywhere.

18:10.022 --> 18:11.289
Please, have a seat.

18:11.356 --> 18:13.791
Um, when I first

18:13.859 --> 18:16.244
took over the glee club,
we needed a male lead.

18:16.328 --> 18:18.746
I heard you singing in
the shower in the locker room.

18:18.831 --> 18:20.665
♪ I'm getting closer ♪

18:20.716 --> 18:25.369
♪ Than I ever
thought I might... ♪

18:25.421 --> 18:26.721
<i>WILL:
REO Speedwagon.</i>

18:26.805 --> 18:28.389
Yeah, you
were really good.

18:28.474 --> 18:30.091
So I planted the pot
in your locker

18:30.175 --> 18:31.809
and blackmailed you
into joining the glee club.

18:31.877 --> 18:33.094
It was wrong.

18:33.162 --> 18:35.146
Although I can't argue
with the results,

18:35.213 --> 18:37.715
I've always hated myself
for doing it.

18:39.568 --> 18:40.818
I'm very sorry, Finn.

18:40.886 --> 18:42.720
But I-I wanted you
to know the truth

18:42.771 --> 18:44.555
before you left, so...

18:46.692 --> 18:49.727
You are so much cooler
than I ever thought you were.

18:53.398 --> 18:55.483
Get out of here.
I'm going to go.

18:57.086 --> 18:58.619
(school bell ringing)

18:58.687 --> 19:00.555
CAROLE: Your graduation gown
with the extra long sleeves

19:00.622 --> 19:02.256
just arrived.

19:04.126 --> 19:05.893
You know, you can have
that thing if you want.

19:05.961 --> 19:07.061
It's probably
the only thing that'll fit

19:07.129 --> 19:09.063
in your tiny little
New York apartment,

19:09.131 --> 19:10.832
but it's yours to have.

19:10.899 --> 19:12.333
I can't help thinking
I let him down, you know?

19:12.401 --> 19:14.002
I feel like I-I could
have spent more time

19:14.069 --> 19:15.436
writing that letter to the Army,

19:15.504 --> 19:17.772
or I could have wrote 50 letters
to the Army,

19:17.840 --> 19:20.208
or I could have started
one of those

19:20.275 --> 19:22.543
letter-writing campaigns,
like... like they had

19:22.611 --> 19:24.312
<i>for Friday Night Lights
or something.</i>

19:24.380 --> 19:25.847
You did everything
you could do.

19:25.914 --> 19:27.749
Your dad made his choices,
and the Army has rules,

19:27.816 --> 19:29.550
and there's nothing
you could have done

19:29.618 --> 19:30.985
about either one
of those things.

19:31.053 --> 19:33.121
I can't help feeling
like something's not right.

19:33.188 --> 19:34.489
I did a lot
of reseah,

19:34.556 --> 19:36.224
trying to get that
honorable discharge status,

19:36.291 --> 19:37.859
and-and he did a lot

19:37.926 --> 19:39.527
of really great things
in Kuwait, you know?

19:39.595 --> 19:42.430
He pulled two soldiers
out of a burning truck.

19:42.498 --> 19:43.831
He saved their lives.

19:43.899 --> 19:45.233
They have kids now my age.

19:45.300 --> 19:46.601
He's a hero.

19:46.668 --> 19:48.903
And how is becoming an actor...

19:48.971 --> 19:51.506
how is that redemption
for a man who did all that?

19:55.110 --> 19:56.978
(sighs)

19:59.415 --> 20:03.384
Everything seems
like it's fallen into place.

20:03.452 --> 20:05.286
Everything but him.

20:06.855 --> 20:08.122
Okay, seniors, the underclassmen

20:08.190 --> 20:09.690
have something
they'd like to say to you.

20:09.758 --> 20:11.459
Come on.

20:13.095 --> 20:14.896
ARTIE: With all
the dedications

20:14.963 --> 20:16.431
being thrown
around McKinley this week,

20:16.498 --> 20:18.616
there was one that we wanted
to make sure didn't get missed.

20:18.667 --> 20:19.834
Finn.

20:21.453 --> 20:22.987
Right now, you're something
I never thought possible

20:23.038 --> 20:24.288
when I first rolled
down these halls.

20:24.339 --> 20:26.490
You're my friend-- our friend.

20:26.542 --> 20:29.260
Even before Glee Club was
kind of cool, you had our backs.

20:29.327 --> 20:30.495
You were on the
football team.

20:30.562 --> 20:31.712
You were one
of the most

20:31.797 --> 20:33.164
popular kids in school.

20:33.215 --> 20:34.732
You had a lot to lose,

20:34.800 --> 20:36.851
and people forget the
sacrifices you made.

20:36.935 --> 20:38.019
We wanted to thank you.

20:38.103 --> 20:41.672
(The Beatles' "In My Life"
begins)

20:41.723 --> 20:45.977
♪ There are places I remember ♪

20:46.028 --> 20:49.180
♪ All my life ♪

20:49.231 --> 20:51.449
♪ Though some have changed ♪

20:51.516 --> 20:55.686
♪ Some forever, not for better ♪

20:55.737 --> 20:58.489
♪ Some have gone ♪

20:58.540 --> 21:00.792
♪ And some remain ♪

21:00.859 --> 21:04.629
♪ All these places
have their moments ♪

21:04.696 --> 21:07.748
♪ With lovers and friends ♪

21:07.833 --> 21:10.001
♪ I still can recall ♪

21:10.052 --> 21:13.704
♪ Some are dead
and some are living ♪

21:15.090 --> 21:17.558
♪ In my life ♪

21:17.643 --> 21:19.210
♪ I loved them all ♪

21:24.049 --> 21:27.602
♪ But of all these
friends and lovers ♪

21:27.686 --> 21:31.105
♪ There is no one ♪

21:31.190 --> 21:33.658
♪ Compares with you ♪

21:33.725 --> 21:37.445
♪ And these memories
lose their meaning ♪

21:37.529 --> 21:40.231
♪ When I think of love ♪

21:40.282 --> 21:42.366
♪ As something new ♪

21:42.417 --> 21:47.004
♪ Though I know I'll never
lose affection ♪

21:47.072 --> 21:52.126
♪ For people and things
that went before ♪

21:52.211 --> 21:56.914
♪ I know I'll often stop
and think about them ♪

21:56.965 --> 21:58.933
♪ In my life ♪

21:59.017 --> 22:01.435
♪ I love you more ♪

22:06.558 --> 22:09.593
♪ In my life... ♪

22:09.645 --> 22:11.562
♪ I love you more. ♪

22:16.434 --> 22:17.768
(song ends)

22:17.819 --> 22:19.120
Yay!

22:24.576 --> 22:26.110
(bell ringing)

22:27.597 --> 22:27.597
+

22:28.377 --> 22:29.911
<i>Who would have thought</i>

22:29.996 --> 22:31.880
<i>I'd end my McKinley days where
I started... back on top?</i>

22:31.964 --> 22:34.216
<i>I got into the school of my
dreams and we won nationals.</i>

22:34.300 --> 22:35.333
<i>Plus I'm feeling stronger
every day.</i>

22:35.384 --> 22:37.368
<i>Everyone else is so emotional.</i>

22:37.420 --> 22:38.970
<i>But I don't feel that way.</i>

22:39.038 --> 22:41.339
<i>I guess I've cried enough tears
for three graduations.</i>

22:41.390 --> 22:43.141
<i>Or maybe it's just hard</i>

22:43.209 --> 22:45.477
<i>to feel weepy when I look
at my friends.</i>

22:45.544 --> 22:47.712
<i>They've grown into such
incredible people.</i>

22:47.763 --> 22:49.181
<i>Nothing's gonna stop
any of them.</i>

22:49.232 --> 22:50.315
<i>Well, maybe one of them.</i>

22:50.382 --> 22:52.150
Countries of
Central America.

22:52.218 --> 22:54.603
Uh, Costa Rica, Honduras...

22:54.687 --> 22:56.571
Crap, I'm blanking.
Come on!

22:56.656 --> 22:59.241
This ain't beach towel
night at Three Rivers.

22:59.325 --> 23:02.577
<i>This school has given us all
so many gifts, me especially.</i>

23:02.662 --> 23:05.113
<i>And I want my last week here
to be about giving back</i>

23:05.198 --> 23:06.665
<i>a little of what I got.</i>

23:06.732 --> 23:08.166
(bell ringing)

23:09.585 --> 23:11.786
This freshman
just gave me a hug

23:11.871 --> 23:13.255
and told me to never change.

23:13.339 --> 23:14.789
Poor thing is too young
to realize

23:14.874 --> 23:16.124
that change can be so good.

23:16.209 --> 23:17.459
Think...

23:17.543 --> 23:18.927
if we hadn't changed,

23:19.011 --> 23:20.262
we would have never been
friends.

23:20.346 --> 23:22.380
Still so weird having you
call me a friend.

23:25.852 --> 23:27.352
There.
What's this?

23:27.419 --> 23:29.771
A Metro North pass
from New York to New Haven.

23:29.856 --> 23:31.940
I got one for me
into New York.

23:32.024 --> 23:33.942
Everybody keeps talking
about staying in touch,

23:34.026 --> 23:36.228
and I want to make sure
that we do.

23:36.279 --> 23:38.429
Thank you.

23:38.481 --> 23:40.649
Thank you.
It's so sweet.

23:40.733 --> 23:43.652
Although I'm still
not 100% sure

23:43.736 --> 23:45.287
that I'm for
teen weddings,

23:45.371 --> 23:47.939
I'm really happy that you
and Finn are together.

23:47.990 --> 23:49.607
You guys were meant to be.

23:49.659 --> 23:50.876
Yeah.

23:50.943 --> 23:52.160
Thank you.

23:52.245 --> 23:53.795
You know, it's weird
'cause that's how

23:53.880 --> 23:55.380
I always felt
about you and Puck.

23:55.447 --> 23:57.299
Ancient history.

23:57.383 --> 23:59.501
But you know what I mean.
When you two were together,

23:59.585 --> 24:02.053
he was really at his best.

24:02.121 --> 24:03.454
Indian Ocean, show me.

24:03.506 --> 24:05.590
It's no use. My brain is like a
Roach Motel,

24:05.641 --> 24:07.392
once the info checks in,
it never checks out.

24:07.459 --> 24:08.760
I'm out of here.

24:08.811 --> 24:10.562
Don't worry. You still get
your Brownie patch

24:10.629 --> 24:12.063
for trying to help a loser
learn something.

24:12.131 --> 24:14.733
I'm not here for a patch.
I'm here because I love you.

24:14.800 --> 24:16.685
You're my first.

24:18.821 --> 24:21.439
I kind of screwed up
that experience, huh?

24:21.490 --> 24:22.691
No regrets.

24:24.493 --> 24:26.828
Cool. 'Cause I always felt
kind of bad about it.

24:26.913 --> 24:28.313
Feel bad about
a lot of things,

24:28.364 --> 24:30.198
but I was an ass for most
of high school.

24:30.283 --> 24:31.700
I really care about you, Puck.

24:31.784 --> 24:33.785
You know what? I know that after
Beth was born,

24:33.836 --> 24:35.287
we weren't really close.

24:35.338 --> 24:37.672
But when two people go though
what we've been through,

24:37.757 --> 24:39.090
you're bonded for life.

24:39.158 --> 24:41.710
If you ever need me,
you know where to find me...

24:41.794 --> 24:43.161
right here in Lima...

24:43.212 --> 24:44.662
repeating my senior
year forever.

24:44.714 --> 24:47.165
I would have never given
my virginity to this guy.

24:47.216 --> 24:49.884
The Puck I fell in love
with had swagger.

24:49.969 --> 24:51.970
And you know what questions
Miss Duesenberry's
gonna ask you,

24:52.021 --> 24:53.855
so you just need
to get your confidence back

24:53.940 --> 24:55.607
so you can get all
that stuff out

24:55.674 --> 24:56.775
of the Roach Motel.

24:56.842 --> 24:57.842
And how am I supposed
to do that?

24:57.893 --> 24:59.361
Like this.

24:59.445 --> 25:01.029
No, no, wait.

25:01.113 --> 25:02.731
I'm not worth it.

25:02.815 --> 25:04.482
Save it for some
Yale guy

25:04.533 --> 25:05.784
who deserves your help.

25:05.851 --> 25:07.485
There's nobody that deserves
it more.

25:07.536 --> 25:08.519
You just have
to remember

25:08.571 --> 25:09.988
the guy you were
when we first met.

25:10.039 --> 25:12.324
You're the guy who caught
the winning touchdown

25:12.375 --> 25:15.026
the only game
the football team
won sophomore year.

25:15.077 --> 25:16.411
You're the guy
that ate

25:16.495 --> 25:18.029
that shaker of pepper
on a dare.

25:18.080 --> 25:19.364
Didn't even puke.

25:19.415 --> 25:21.049
Will you let me kiss you?

25:21.133 --> 25:24.169
I guess I'd be kind of rude
if I refused.

25:24.220 --> 25:26.054
You know, Puckerman...

25:26.138 --> 25:28.006
you got this.

25:32.812 --> 25:34.846
♪ ♪

25:36.349 --> 25:37.983
<i>Funny thing about a kiss.</i>

25:38.050 --> 25:40.068
<i>If it comes at the right time
from the right girl,</i>

25:40.152 --> 25:41.319
<i>it can be like magic.</i>

25:41.387 --> 25:42.854
<i>It can bring you back to life</i>

25:42.905 --> 25:44.239
<i>like CPR, but with tongues.</i>

25:44.323 --> 25:46.441
<i>It can take away
